article.headline: Arizona St. 76, Delaware St. 34
article.story: TEMPE, Ariz. -- Derek Glasser had 14 points and nine assists and Victor Rudd had a career-high 15 points to lead a balanced attack as Arizona State overwhelmed Delaware State 76-34 on Saturday. The Sun Devils (7-3) took control with a 23-0 run that began six minutes into the game to take a 32-8 lead. Glasser made two of Arizona State's 10 3-point field goals and committed only one turnover. Rudd, a reserve forward who was ineligible for the first three games of the season, made 6 of 7 field-goal attempts and had three 3-pointers while playing in the later stages. Rudd had seven points in four previous games. Frisco Sandidge led Delaware State (4-4) with 12 points, and Marcus Neal had 11. The Hornets shot 25 percent from the field.
